practices.notes: First ever practice wrestling. Was a beginner type class for fundamentals. I was able to grasp some basics alright but hesitant to have direct conflict and press up aggressively on opponent. Afraid of injuring self and others. Most guys weren't too much of a challenge in beginner level. One I had to actually take it easy on. But one guy threw my off easily and quickly. Knew the moves better and could exhaust me. After grappling with him I was the most gassed I have ever been in my life. My head was pounding and my heart was thumping like a double kick drum. I thought I was either going to pass out or throw up. It was incredible how everything else melts away in the heat of such moments. Even right after I recall nothing but concern for breathing and recovery. Pure focus. One hell of a shock to the system. The day after everything was sore. Every muscle, every fibre. Brutal but a thrilling new journey began.

Got an ankle pick. But gruelling physically. Even early into the workout in practice my legs were exhausted and I was gased.

Second practice with the wrestling shoes. Make a great difference. Technique came in for a moment or two in some takedowns during the double leg and high crotch. Still afraid to tuck my head in for the single leg. Afraid of neck injuries and getting tossed around.

Learning opponent styles. Some hand fight a lot. Others always look for the single leg and shoot hard and fast, less upper body Greco Roman Focus. Others move strangely with too much thoughts allowing me to find openings because they try to figure me out too much.
